modules.description: Provides methods to show and hide a native activity indicator, with support for customizing the message and color. Works with boolean flags to control visibility and string values for display text. Used to signal ongoing operations in mobile apps, such as during data loading or form submission.

Displays a progress indicator with a custom message and removes it, operating on string and unit types. It is used to signal ongoing operations in mobile applications during asynchronous tasks. The show function updates the UI with a message, while hide clears the indicator.
